The Management of Federal Medical Centre, Abeokuta ,Idi-Aba, Abeokuta, Ogun State, has threatened to henceforth take a  drastic action against  patients’ relatives that assaulted its medical personnel. The management reacted to the recent assault on the medical personnel by a patient’s relative, saying it would not be business as usual. The acting Medical Director, Dr Fidelis Ojeblenu, issued the threat during a press briefing held at the centre on Tuesday. Ojeblenu frowned at the continuous attacks on the FMC medical personnels and destruction of hospital property by members of the public. Recall that a relative of a patient attacked a medical worker in the centre on July 6. The relative, who was said to be infuriated by the death of his family member who was a  patient at the hospital. The acting MD at the press briefing said, “We have overhauled the security architecture of the hospital in readiness to forestall future occurrences. Plain-clothed security agents are on ground to apprehend future culprits.” The state Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, said the suspect would be charged to court after the completion of investigation. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com